Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. Mix eggs, milk, ricotta cheese, basil, and mozzarella cheese in a bowl. Add salt and pepper to the bowl and mix very well. Place1/2 Cup of the marinara sauce into the bottom of an 8 x 8 baking dish. Line the bottom of the baking dish with 4 lasagna noodles. Place 1/3 of the amount of ricotta filling across the first layer of noodles. Follow the cheese mixture with 1/3 of the amount of sausage, sprinkled evenly across the ricotta layer. Add 1/2 Cup of marinara sauce on top of the sausage layer; be sure to spread it evenly. Repeat the layering process until the remaining noodles are on the top. Place 1 Cup of marinara sauce across the top of the noodles. Bake in oven for 40 minutes.